caption: I am obsessed. I decided to search for vegan food on DoorDash to see if any new places were added, not expecting to find anything and LOW AND BEHOLD... the Broccoli Bar was there.  My friends and I had a really hard time not ordering the entire menu. Everything looks delicious. We did get a lot of stuff and it was all DELICIOUS. I want to eat it basically every day. I’m so happy it exists.
Thrilled to have a fresh, tasty, quick and interesting place in the neighborhood. Very friendly folks, too. Toddler loves the dumplings and we love the dry rub.
Everything is delicious
If you’re vegan or even if you’re not vegan, this place is AMAZING. Yummy food and wonderful people running the place. Fun atmosphere, must visit!

Love love love The Broccoli Bar! I'm addicted to their Tempura Broccoli with Maple Sriracha sauce OMG just bomb.com as my sister in law says. I've ordered the Medium Broccoli Boat ($8) twice for pick up now. Pictured you can see the order of Tempura x2 and Stir Fry x1. They have also written a sweet and personalized note on the paper bag for both pick ups, super sweet and very personal. If you have kids, this is THE way to make them like broccoli if they don't. I know for a fact if I had The Broccoli Bar in my life as a kid I would have gladly increased my intake of broccoli!
I love this place!! Food taste amazing!! Always fresh!!!
Just ordered lunch from here for the first time and wow...the chopped cheese is so dang good. Fries too. And delivery was super fast...in love all around!

Best of the Best and I mean that. I'd take non Vegan friends here and I assure you they'd love it. Came in unexpectedly and Chef Vogelman was cool and genuine and talked with us and you could tell his sense of community and chef owned sensibility infuses the Broccoli Bar with so much of his spirit. We had vegan burgers and fries and also got a stir fry for the road; man!! I can't say enough good things. A couple days later I'm already craving the Broccoli Bar. Long may the reign! Great place, great atmosphere, GREAT FOOD.
Onion rings and cheese fries were outstanding! The hot bar was good too!

Such a fun and hip joint. I already love broccoli but I feel like my meek here made me love it even more! I got the tempura, pakora, and dumplings. Delish. If they’re on DeliverZero I’d definitely order all the time!
The pakoras and tempura are really tasty. My daughter, husband and I had a fine lunch. We're coming here again!

Amazing food, so delicious, fresh and great value! On one occasion we weren't able to pick up our food on time and when we finally arrived a few hours later, they made our order (again) fresh for us, we were happy to reheat because it keeps well, but they lovely team insisted. Yummy food and super friendly staff.

I’ve had a few different dishes and have been constantly astonished with how great everything is - the Ruben sandwich is beyond anything I could imagine could be made without real pastrami - this Ruben is as good as it gets. Today I tried the burger - simply amazing.  This little restaurant is worth a try for anyone who wants to eat vegan or completely uninterested in plant based food.

Great food, such a cool concept!  I tried large plate for the hot bar.  The fried options were unreal.  The blackened roasted one was a little overcooked, and was missing the crispiness you get right when it's out of the oven.  The ones with the batter on the outside were fairly crispy, but I guess if they wanna preserve the crispiness on the roasted ones, they need to store it in a different style of heating container that keeps it dry.  The steamed broccoli was pretty good but not amazing, maybe could have used a more pronounced sauce, but I guess they gotta have a healthy light option for some ppl.  All vegan! :D
So happy this place is here. Dumplings, pakora, and tempura are fantastic.
Love this place. Delicious food, efficient delivery and well packed.
The entire menu is delicious and the portions are very generous

So delicious!!! I got a small hot bar bowl for my first time and next time and every time - LARGE. Everything was so delicious!! The sauces, the food, the rice. New favorite vegan spot in bed stuy for sure.
I'm a super fan of the Rick Ruben, Disco Fries and the Burger ♥️ Looking forward to trying out all the options on the menu
It's poetry the fact that a bbq brisket place is replaced by a vegan broccoli bar. This is great "grub food." Fast, filling, affordable and really good! Five stars for sure

Broccoli Bar pushes broccoli TO THE MAX!!!!!!!  This s*it gets deep fried, bbq’d, dumpling’d, the works. Turns out all the things vegans do to cauliflower work way better with broccoli. The flavor is 😍 and the texture is 🤤. Bonus points for being so filling- idk how because it’s just broccoli and rice. A TRIUMPH!
Amazing food and great people. All the hot bar food was delicious but especially loved the vegan Reuben sandwich. Plus the owner is a rad dude. Grab yourself some grub.
A giant plate of food for $8, and all of it is wonderful
Everything 🥦.....yummy
Literally the best meal I’ve ever had😍 definitely recommend. I would be vegan if I could eat this every single day for every meal - and I would. So so tasty and amazing. Great value as well

When i first heard that this was vegan and all broccoli based i was like uh-oh, that can’t be good. but then i went, and it was one of the best meals i’ve ever had. everyone should go, it was amazing!!!! 😍😍😍
Get the carrot or involve the carrot somehow.
love this place, a much needed addition to the neighborhood!

Let me start off by say my husband and I have been here a few times and we generally enjoy the food. Usually we go during the week though and perhaps that was the difference. Yesterday (Sunday) I went to get us a lunch, we attempting to try all of the sandwiches because we’ve tried the entire menu otherwise. I ordered two sandwiches (both with extra cheese sauce on the side) and an order of pakora in person at the window. A total of 6 people got their food before I did and I realize they make the sandwiches to order but my total wait time was nearly 30 minutes. During which time they’d already packed the order of pakora. Before I left I asked if the extra cheese was in the bag, the young lady at the counter went to ensure I had them and was told they were in the bag. When I got home (I live around the corner 400ft to be exact) the pakora and rice were cold and sodden. And of course no cheese sauce, not extra, not any. I was so disappointed and disheartened by the wait I didn’t bother to go back but I sincerely wanted to because I was so upset. The food is worth it but I’d recommend going on a weekday.

Really really wanted to love this- broccoli is my favorite vegetable and as a vegan I’m always looking for fun places to try. Set a pick-up time for 5:45pm (instead of the default for 5:30pm that was suggested on the website). Got the text my order was ready at 5:30pm anyway. Food was super cold, and soggy, and really lacked flavor. The best part of the meal were the fries I added on to the “Brocc Pocket”. There was no option to modify an order even though on the website it said to add a sellers note upon checkout. Super dissatisfied and sad. Even the workers inside were lackluster and when I mentioned how excited I was to pick up my food to try it they didn’t even respond lol.  Hard pass!  *UPDATE*  I went back (thanks to the response and action of the co-owner). The food was hot and the “po boy” style sandwich was incredible. The staff was kind. Thank you!
Broccoli is delicious! Especially when fried. Try the pakora and you won't be disappointed

This is the vegan restaurant we have all been waiting for in Fort Greene! The broccoli boats are amazing and the new sandwich menu kicks a$$. Absolutely love the Banh Greene and the B.I.G. Burger. Can’t wait to try everything else! Don’t sleep on the BBQ dry rub broccoli, it slaps💚🥦
I would go back here.  They sell broccoli 🥦.
Fresh and tasty food, awesome vibe, and wonderful staff.
Bomb knew spot on Fort Green. The selection are savory and delicious. And they give free samples.
Half tempura, half BBQ rub — both delicious. Friendly people ✨
Really really tasty new place! All around nice atmosphere, delicious foods, friendly people and pleasant energy.
